requests.name: Send Email
requests.description: Sending Email

queryParams.description: Required. API key of the master account (Only the master account can have sub-accounts)
Address(es) to blind copy the email to

The text/html version of the email; this field may be encoded in 7-bit, 8-bit, quoted-printable, or base64.nNotes:n– Even though bodytext and bodyhtml are both optional, at least one of them must be provided for the email to be valid.n– If sending non-ASCII characters within your content, we recommend using Base64 encoding, as this has proven the most reliable way to preserve special characters across email providers.

The plain/text version of the email; this field may be encoded in Base64 (recommended), quoted-printable, 8-bit, or 7-bit.nNotes:n– Even though bodytext and bodyhtml are both optional, at least one of them must be provided for the email to be valid.n– If sending non-ASCII characters within your contentu00a0you must Base64-encode it first, as this has proven the most reliable way to preserve special characters across email providers.
Address(es) to copy the email to
Additional comments about the message.
Required. Sender email address
A hint from the originator on how important the message is. Can take values of either high, normal or low. Not related to transmission speed.
One or more message identifier(s) of the original message(s) to which the current message is a reply.
A comma-separated list of important words and phrases useful for recipient.
A unique message identifier that can be passed in via the api and override the Dyn automatically generated message id.
Values are either normal, urgent, or non-urgent. This header can influence transmission speed and delivery.
The message identifier(s) of other message(s) to which the current message may be related.
The date and time by which a reply is requested. Date-time should be in local time format such as Thu, 13 Feb 2013 23:32:54 -0330.

The email address for the recipient to reply to. If left blank, defaults to the from address. The format can either be an email address or a properly formatted from header (example: “From Name” <example@email.com>).
The date and time that a message is resent in the same format as replyby.
u00a0Email address of sender for filtering. Must be on the current Approved Sender list. u00a0if using a GET request, it is best practice to encode special characters such as the “at symbol” (@).
How sensitive it is to disclose this message with values that can be either personal, private or company confidential.
Required. The subject of the email being sent.
Required. Address(es) the email will be sent to
Any additional custom X-headers to send in the email
